  "_exec_summary": [
    {
      "ESSeqNum": 3,
      "FacilityID": 1000089964,
      "SummaryText": "actions developed, implemented and tracked to completion to prevent future occurrence. Besides minor releases of material inside the plant which have not resulted in personnel exposures or illnesses, there have not been any incidents or releases resulting in off-site consequences at the ARLANXEO, USA LLC,Orange site in the last five years. As a consequence, there is no report documented in Section 6, Five Year Accident History of the RMP report.\r\n\r\nEmergency Response Program: \r\nThe ARLANXEO, USA LLC, Orange site maintains a detailed emergency response plan. A trained emergency brigade and a hazardous material response team are maintained on site.  Disaster drills are conducted on site at least once a year and the site participates in local area emergency response drills.  In addition, the ARLANXEO, USA LLC, Orange Plant participates in the Orange County Local Emergency Planning Committee (LEPC) and Regional Mutual Aid Committees. The response time for the local emergency management team is less than fifteen minutes to the plant. There are warning lights and signs on the roads leading to the plant to warn motorists in the event of a plant emergency.  The signs are activated by the local Police Department and maintained by the LEPC."
    },
    {
      "ESSeqNum": 2,
      "FacilityID": 1000089964,
      "SummaryText": "(MOC) program across the plant with updated procedures, incident and near hit reporting, preventive and corrective actions, and tracking of action items to closure. The site also maintains a mechanical integrity program for equipment, piping and vessel inspections, testing and repairs.  \r\n\r\nMaintenance and improvement of Health, Safety and Environmental systems are ongoing at this facility and training takes place throughout the year.  Safety and environmental recommendations from employees, whether made during formal sessions like Process Hazard Analyses (PHA) or upon observation of a potential hazard, are investigated with corrective actions developed, implemented and tracked to completion in order to prevent future occurrence.\r\n\r\nSignificant safety improvements occurring over the last five years include a Health, Safety and Environmental Management System, upgrades in fire protection deluge systems, updated emergency response drills and training, implementation of PHA action items, and implementation of facility siting and building improvement projects.  All non-essential personnel are located away from potential areas for overpressure scenarios or explosion hazards.\r\n\r\nLeak Detection Systems:\r\nThe site maintains a third party on-site Leak Detection and Repairs (LDAR) program. Detected leaks are reported on routine basis and necessary repairs are conducted to avoid major release incidents. There are hydrocarbons detectors located throughout the plant and are inspected and tested at least once a year. In addition, emergency shut-off valves and excess flow check valves are installed in discharge lines of major vessels throughout the plant, and are periodically inspected and tested to avoid catastrophic releases. \r\n\r\n5 Year Accident History: \r\nARLANXEO, USA LLC, Orange site maintains exceptional safety, health and environmental record. All incidents and releases are documented and reported in an electronic data system. Every incident is investigated with corrective"
    },
    {
      "ESSeqNum": 1,
