      "SummaryText": "hydrocarbons solvents and two chemicals that are used in quantities above the threshold quantities as defined in EPA 40 CFR Part 68 Risk Management Planning regulation. The hydrocarbons solvents are 1,3-butadiene and 1-butene.  The other two chemicals are chlorine and anhydrous ammonia, which are primarily used in the Utilities department. \r\n\r\nThe ARLANXEO, USA LLC, Orange, Texas site supports many outreach programs for the community including, the United Way, a Community Relations Committee, and an employee sponsored diversity program (MOSAIC). The facility maintains a ISO 14001 standard.\r\n\r\nRecent Changes and Improvements: \r\nMost recent changes and improvements includes, shut down of the EPDM (Keltan) manufacturing unit, process enhancement at the LiBR rubber manufacturing unit and Boiler #5 installation project. Installation of the Boiler #5 project is necessary due to termination of the contract between ARLANXEO and the COGEN plant which supplied steam and electricity to the Orange site and a neighbor Chevron Chemical plant.  \r\n\r\nProcess Safety and Risk Management:  \r\nThe ARLANXEO, USA LLC, Orange Plant is a PSM covered site. It is in compliance with the OSHA PSM Regulation 29 CFR 1910.119 and EPA 40 CFR Part 68 Risk Management Planning regulations.  All the manufacturing units comply with the fourteen PSM elements, and are considered to be Program Level III process under Risk Management Planning. \r\n\r\nThe site PSM programs include:  \r\nEmployee Participation \r\nProcess Safety Information\r\nProcess Hazard Analyses\r\nOperating Procedures\r\nEmployee Training\r\nContractor Safety\r\nPre-Start Up Safety Review\r\nMechanical Integrity\r\nSafe work Practices\r\nManagement of Change\r\nIncident Investigation\r\nEmergency Planning and Response\r\nCompliance Audits\r\nTrade Secrets\r\n\r\nAccidental Release Prevention and Emergency Response Policies:  \r\nRelease Prevention:\r\nHandling of hazardous materials undergoes a rigo